From: aorus-5090-egpu <noreply@example.invalid>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 13:45:00 +1000
Subject: [PATCH] Lever M-recover: scaffolding for in-driver recovery state machine

Per-pdev struct + module parameters + sysfs counters + workqueue plumbing
for AORUS Lever M-recover (Phase 4, 2026-05-06). This is Commit 1 of 3 in
patch series 0016 — scaffolding ONLY, no behaviour change.

Empirical justification:
  archive/boot-recovery-fail-2026-05-06-125648/ — proved that the L4
  helper (Lever R Tier 1 v3, aorus-egpu-wpr2-recovery.service) is
  structurally race-prone with userspace bind-retriers. Recovery
  succeeds reliably ONLY when no other userspace authority concurrently
  accesses /dev/nvidia0. Single-arbiter is unavoidable; only the driver
  has unconditional priority.

Mechanism (delivered by commits 2-3 building on this scaffolding):
  - Boot-time WPR2-stuck: probe-time MMIO check at BAR0+0x88a828
    (NV_HUBMMU_PRI_MMU_WPR2_ADDR_HI), schedule workqueue to call
    pci_reset_bus() on upstream Thunderbolt switch downstream port,
    return -EPROBE_DEFER for kernel re-probe
  - Runtime AER: error_detected returns NEED_RESET; kernel does bus
    reset; slot_reset/resume callbacks re-init driver state

This Commit 1 (scaffolding) deliverables:
  - struct tb_egpu_lever_m_recover with workqueue + atomic counters
  - 3 module params: NVreg_TbEgpuLeverMRecoverEnable (kill switch),
    NVreg_TbEgpuLeverMMaxAttempts (default 3),
    NVreg_TbEgpuLeverMResetSettleMs (default 500ms)
  - 4 sysfs counters: tb_egpu_lever_m_{fires,successes,surrenders,
    last_fire_jiffies} (read-only, 0444)
  - Hooked into nv_pci_probe (init) and nv_pci_remove_helper (stop)
    next to existing Q-watchdog calls
  - Work handler is a no-op stub; behaviour identical to Lever M-base

See docs/lever-M-recover-design.md for full design.

Sovereign layer: L1 (NVIDIA fork) — this is the architectural destination
that retires aorus-egpu-wpr2-recovery.service per
docs/service-retirement-roadmap.md upon n>=10 PROVEN cold-cold-boot
reproductions through this in-driver path.

Tasks: #62
---
diff --git a/kernel-open/common/inc/nv-linux.h b/kernel-open/common/inc/nv-linux.h
index 1ce779f9..004c8883 100644
--- a/kernel-open/common/inc/nv-linux.h
+++ b/kernel-open/common/inc/nv-linux.h
@@ -1441,6 +1441,13 @@ typedef struct nv_linux_state_s {
      * heartbeat kthread state. Forward-declared opaque pointer to
      * avoid pulling nv-qwatchdog.h into common headers. */
     struct tb_egpu_qwatchdog *qwd;
+
+    /* AORUS Lever M-recover (Phase 4, 2026-05-06): per-device in-driver
+     * recovery state — workqueue + sysfs counters + retry budget.
+     * Forward-declared opaque pointer; full struct in
+     * nv-lever-m-recover.h. NULL if NVreg_TbEgpuLeverMRecoverEnable=0
+     * at module load (kill switch). */
+    struct tb_egpu_lever_m_recover *lever_m;
 } nv_linux_state_t;
 
 extern nv_linux_state_t *nv_linux_devices;
